Detectives say they have apprehended a 'person of interest' in the horrific murder of New York Red Bulls soccer coach Michael Jones -- who was slashed and stabbed on the sidewalk in an attack so brutal that his ear was hacked off.

Police are currently interviewing the man who they believe was captured by security cameras calmly walking away from the spot in New York's Greenwich Village where Mr Jones, 25, was found dying about 4.30am Sunday.

Mr Jones was reportedly returning to a friend's apartment after night of visiting upscale clubs when he was attacked.

Video shows Mr Jones walking with his suspected killer. An argument ensures before the attacker slashed Mr Jones' throat and stabbed him in the abdomen and chest.

