Mr Jones, a native of Liverpool, 
England, was beloved by the young soccer players he coached for the Armonk United youth soccer team in Westchester, New York. Friends and
co-workers said he had a gift for the game.

'He coached two of my three sons and was just a great guy. He cared about what he did, and was very dedicated,' Mark Fischer, who oversees referees in the Westchester league, told the Post. 'The kids loved him.'

Officers are still trying to figure out what provoked the horrendous killing and why Mr Jones was seen walking down the street with the man at 4am after leaving his girlfriend earlier in the night.

Police say he began the evening spending time with his girlfriend at the apartment of one of her male friends on West 14th Street in Greenwich Village.

Mr Jones left her about 11.30pm and said he was planning to meet a friend at the Standard Hotel bar in the Meatpacking district.

