Police are still trying to determine a 
motive for the gruesome murder but do not believe it was a robbery as 
the victim's iPhone was still at the scene, covered in blood on the 
ground.

No arrests have been made in the ongoing investigation.

Residents of the West Village neighborhood who consider it a safe residential area are stunned.

'It's horrible. I've been living here my whole life,' said Sarah Cohen, 22, a chef who lives nearby. 'People are starting families here. There are religious institutions. How are we supposed to have all that if we can't keep residents safe?'

